WEBVTT

1
00:01:31.579 --> 00:01:33.159
Ohh!

2
00:01:33.284 --> 00:01:37.055
Nirvana.

3
00:01:40.182 --> 00:01:42.185
Why weren't we born rich?

4
00:01:42.351 --> 00:01:45.005
'Cause our parents didn't have money.

5
00:01:45.130 --> 00:01:46.481
Hmm.

6
00:01:50.772 --> 00:01:52.279
Shall we go on our yacht. darling?

7
00:01:52.404 --> 00:01:55.073
Which one?

8
00:02:04.449 --> 00:02:05.325
Slow down!

9
00:02:05.450 --> 00:02:08.336
Oh. you wish!

10
00:02:11.573 --> 00:02:14.234
Gilda?

11
00:02:14.359 --> 00:02:17.828
Where do you think...
You're going?

12
00:02:31.859 --> 00:02:33.670
Catch me if you can.

13
00:02:35.913 --> 00:02:37.032
Oh. I can.

14
00:02:40.585 --> 00:02:45.322
Gilda. come on.

15
00:03:14.919 --> 00:03:16.329
- What was that?
- What?

16
00:03:16.454 --> 00:03:17.897
I think I heard a car.

17
00:03:18.022 --> 00:03:19.332
No. you didn't.

18
00:03:19.457 --> 00:03:22.635
Rocky. stop.
Go look out the window.

19
00:03:22.760 --> 00:03:24.812
- Now?
- Yeah. go.

20
00:03:28.366 --> 00:03:30.367
Somebody's here. you're right.
Come on. let's go.

21
00:03:33.104 --> 00:03:34.781
No. no. not the door.
The window.

22
00:03:34.906 --> 00:03:36.023
Come on.

23
00:03:41.446 --> 00:03:42.455
You got it?

24
00:03:42.580 --> 00:03:43.765
Yeah.

25
00:03:43.931 --> 00:03:45.115
Ohh!

26
00:03:46.851 --> 00:03:48.103
You okay?

27
00:03:48.269 --> 00:03:50.997
Yeah. I'm fine.

28
00:03:51.122 --> 00:03:54.367
Come on.
Let's go. Hurry up.

29
00:03:54.492 --> 00:03:55.861
Hyuh!

30
00:03:57.512 --> 00:03:59.114
Rocky. what are you doing?

31
00:04:23.905 --> 00:04:25.989
Come on!

32
00:04:33.998 --> 00:04:35.592
Are you still dizzy?

33
00:04:35.717 --> 00:04:37.277
I'm all right.

34
00:04:37.402 --> 00:04:39.245
Well. your liver enzymes
are elevated.

35
00:04:39.370 --> 00:04:42.048
and we found traces of a neurotoxin

36
00:04:42.173 --> 00:04:45.485
in your blood: Phtx3.
which is usually associated

37
00:04:45.610 --> 00:04:47.220
with a spider bite.

38
00:04:47.345 --> 00:04:48.521
Lucky you didn't get more of it.

39
00:04:48.646 --> 00:04:51.624
or it would've paralyzed your lungs.

40
00:04:51.749 --> 00:04:56.362
Well. if you feel lightheaded
or feverish. come on back.

41
00:04:56.487 --> 00:04:58.355
All right.

42
00:05:01.826 --> 00:05:03.303
They find anything wrong with you?

43
00:05:03.469 --> 00:05:05.321
Just a few toxins in the blood.

44
00:05:05.446 --> 00:05:07.991
Just a few toxins?
Like the kind that can kill you?

45
00:05:08.116 --> 00:05:09.442
Well. apparently not.

46
00:05:09.567 --> 00:05:10.877
You gonna be okay?

47
00:05:11.002 --> 00:05:12.078
How do I look?

48
00:05:12.203 --> 00:05:14.047
Like a cop who's been
working all night.

49
00:05:14.172 --> 00:05:15.748
Aw. that's funny. Hank.
That's how you look.

50
00:05:15.873 --> 00:05:17.901
Well. then you look good.

51
00:05:20.011 --> 00:05:21.237
Marie.

52
00:05:21.403 --> 00:05:22.956
She's not stable.

53
00:05:23.081 --> 00:05:24.866
We can't allow anyone
in the I.C.U. yet.

54
00:05:25.032 --> 00:05:26.226
Well. when can I talk to her?

55
00:05:26.351 --> 00:05:28.962
After we're done running the tests.

56
00:05:29.087 --> 00:05:32.432
We can't risk letting her
slip back into a coma.

57
00:05:32.557 --> 00:05:35.585
I'll call you the minute
we know something.

58
00:05:40.551 --> 00:05:43.817
I.D. anyone who wants
access to the room.

59
00:05:46.204 --> 00:05:47.180
How is she?

60
00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:48.581
Well. she came out of the coma.

61
00:05:48.706 --> 00:05:50.100
but they're still running tests.

62
00:05:50.266 --> 00:05:51.584
So when did the attack happen?

63
00:05:51.709 --> 00:05:53.603
About ten minutes after I got here.

64
00:05:53.769 --> 00:05:55.722
She came up behind me.

65
00:05:55.847 --> 00:05:57.290
She had a syringe in her hand.

66
00:05:57.415 --> 00:05:58.900
How do you know she wasn't a nurse?

67
00:05:59.066 --> 00:06:02.595
Well. she stuck a needle
into me. and she ran away.

68
00:06:02.720 --> 00:06:04.406
Well. you think you can identify her?

69
00:06:04.572 --> 00:06:05.665
Yeah. she should be
on the security tapes.

70
00:06:05.790 --> 00:06:06.766
I grabbed them when I got here.

71
00:06:06.891 --> 00:06:08.301
They're on their way to the precinct.

72
00:06:08.426 --> 00:06:09.836
Let's take a look at those tapes.

73
00:06:09.961 --> 00:06:11.304
If we got another killer
on our hands.

74
00:06:11.429 --> 00:06:13.239
we better get on this.

75
00:06:26.719 --> 00:06:28.763
When's the last time you saw
your aunt before this?

76
00:06:28.929 --> 00:06:30.857
Not for a couple years.

77
00:06:30.982 --> 00:06:33.016
I don't know what she's been up to.

78
00:06:35.853 --> 00:06:36.980
That's her.

79
00:06:38.981 --> 00:06:39.983
Was she alone?

80
00:06:40.149 --> 00:06:42.035
She's the only one I saw.

81
00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:44.237
It'll be difficult to make
an I.D. from the back.

82
00:06:44.403 --> 00:06:46.114
- Is this all you got?
- Yeah.

83
00:06:47.865 --> 00:06:51.828
Let me know if you get
something we can work with.

84
00:06:51.994 --> 00:06:54.372
Dude. what'd your aunt do
to piss off so many people?

85
00:06:54.538 --> 00:06:56.182
She work for the government
or something?

86
00:06:56.307 --> 00:06:59.085
I had a D.U.I. out on
highway 2 about an hour ago.

87
00:06:59.251 --> 00:07:00.711
Driver's got some crazy story

88
00:07:00.836 --> 00:07:02.172
about her boyfriend being attacked.

89
00:07:02.338 --> 00:07:03.798
Name's Gilda Darner.

90
00:07:09.454 --> 00:07:10.763
What do you think?

91
00:07:10.888 --> 00:07:14.559
Ah. grown up way too fast.
Single parent. if she has any.

92
00:07:14.725 --> 00:07:17.670
Takes way too many chances.
and looks for excitement

93
00:07:17.795 --> 00:07:20.873
- in all the wrong places.
- Sounds like me.

94
00:07:20.998 --> 00:07:22.317
Yeah.
Look how you turned out.

95
00:07:26.753 --> 00:07:29.005
Gilda Darner?

96
00:07:40.017 --> 00:07:42.779
This is the house.
This is where it happened.

97
00:07:42.904 --> 00:07:44.881
Somebody got here before us.

98
00:07:47.024 --> 00:07:49.526
Stay in the car.

99
00:07:54.365 --> 00:07:56.776
What are you doing here?
I haven't even called it in yet.

100
00:07:56.901 --> 00:07:59.896
- Well. what do you got?
- Breaking and entering.

101
00:08:00.062 --> 00:08:01.497
Mr. and Mrs. Rabe
got back from Seattle

102
00:08:01.622 --> 00:08:04.617
a couple hours ago.
found their house broken into.

103
00:08:04.742 --> 00:08:06.886
Somebody raided the fridge.
hit the liquor cabinet.

104
00:08:07.011 --> 00:08:09.505
tried on some clothes.
and test-drove a couple of beds.

105
00:08:09.630 --> 00:08:10.640
Any sign of violence?

106
00:08:10.765 --> 00:08:12.759
No. No blood.
No body parts.

107
00:08:12.884 --> 00:08:15.120
Only stains we've come up with
are wine and whoopee.

108
00:08:15.286 --> 00:08:17.096
- Who's her missing boy toy?
- Says his name's Rocky.

109
00:08:17.221 --> 00:08:18.581
We're still trying to figure out

110
00:08:18.747 --> 00:08:21.292
how much of her story is true.

111
00:08:21.458 --> 00:08:23.962
Well. she's copping to
the B and E. so some of it is.

112
00:08:24.128 --> 00:08:25.638
Where are the owners?

113
00:08:25.763 --> 00:08:27.597
Upstairs.

114
00:08:28.599 --> 00:08:30.994
Somebody was sleeping in our bed.

115
00:08:31.119 --> 00:08:32.211
Sleep had nothing to do

116
00:08:32.336 --> 00:08:34.113
with what they were doing in our bed.

117
00:08:34.238 --> 00:08:36.182
You have an alarm system?

118
00:08:36.307 --> 00:08:39.002
Well. we've been a little lax
in using it lately.

119
00:08:39.127 --> 00:08:40.253
We're pretty remote out here.

120
00:08:40.378 --> 00:08:41.649
I mean. we've never had
a problem before.

121
00:08:43.477 --> 00:08:45.615
You should see the living room.

122
00:08:47.302 --> 00:08:50.163
Nothing was stolen?

123
00:08:50.288 --> 00:08:53.072
Don't know yet.
Nothing obvious.

124
00:08:54.101 --> 00:08:55.410
You have quite a collection.

125
00:08:56.462 --> 00:08:59.188
Is that a Fijian war club?

126
00:08:59.313 --> 00:09:01.006
Yes. actually. it is.

127
00:09:01.131 --> 00:09:04.010
And a new Guinea tribal fork.
This is some valuable stuff.

128
00:09:04.135 --> 00:09:05.670
You know your aboriginal art.

129
00:09:05.836 --> 00:09:07.672
I've never seen one like that before.

130
00:09:07.838 --> 00:09:09.482
It's Germanic.
Uh. very rare.

131
00:09:09.607 --> 00:09:11.851
From about 900 A.D.

132
00:09:11.976 --> 00:09:13.086
We belong to organizations

133
00:09:13.211 --> 00:09:15.263
that protect native land
from development.

134
00:09:15.429 --> 00:09:17.682
There's a lot of rich
cultural heritage disappearing.

135
00:09:17.848 --> 00:09:19.358
and we're trying
to protect what's left

136
00:09:19.483 --> 00:09:20.693
both locally and globally...

137
00:09:20.818 --> 00:09:22.896
Honey. I think you're getting
a little irrelevant.

138
00:09:23.062 --> 00:09:24.897
Well. you have
to respect your ancestors.

139
00:09:25.022 --> 00:09:26.024
Right. detective?

140
00:09:26.190 --> 00:09:27.500
I had to respect mine.

141
00:09:27.625 --> 00:09:30.043
otherwise. I couldn't
sit down for a week.

142
00:09:32.096 --> 00:09:34.073
Anyone else have access
to the house when you were away?

143
00:09:34.198 --> 00:09:35.617
Just our cleaning people.

144
00:09:35.783 --> 00:09:37.952
And our son Barry.
who's staying with friends.

145
00:09:38.118 --> 00:09:39.779
And our neighbors. the Colberts.

146
00:09:39.904 --> 00:09:41.372
who check on our house
from time to time

147
00:09:41.538 --> 00:09:43.666
when we're out of town.

148
00:09:47.078 --> 00:09:48.554
Fijian war club?

149
00:09:48.679 --> 00:09:50.173
Second wife was an anthropologist.

150
00:09:50.339 --> 00:09:52.800
So there were two people
in that house.

151
00:09:52.966 --> 00:09:54.302
So where's Gilda's boyfriend?

152
00:09:54.468 --> 00:09:57.964
My guess. Rocky's home
right now. sleeping it off.

153
00:10:13.504 --> 00:10:16.416
Ohh! Ah.

154
00:10:23.869 --> 00:10:32.590
<font color="#3399FF">Sync and correction by Mlmlte</font>
<font color="#3399FF">www.addic7ed.com</font>

155
00:10:36.098 --> 00:10:38.591
So you do this?

156
00:10:38.716 --> 00:10:40.716
Break into homes. party hardy.

157
00:10:40.841 --> 00:10:43.393
- We were just having fun.
- Illegal fun.

158
00:10:43.559 --> 00:10:45.855
Gilda. you said after you
dropped out of the window.

159
00:10:45.980 --> 00:10:47.123
you heard Rocky scream.

160
00:10:47.248 --> 00:10:48.773
you started running away
from the house.

161
00:10:48.939 --> 00:10:50.276
and something chased you.

162
00:10:50.401 --> 00:10:52.996
Yes.

163
00:10:53.121 --> 00:10:55.715
It's my fault.

164
00:10:55.840 --> 00:10:57.573
I should've gone back for him.

165
00:10:58.897 --> 00:11:01.771
but...I just left him there.

166
00:11:01.896 --> 00:11:04.507
I left him there.

167
00:11:04.632 --> 00:11:08.459
Please. Please. you've gotta
do something.

168
00:11:21.555 --> 00:11:25.061
Gilda. do you have any idea
who was chasing you?

169
00:11:25.186 --> 00:11:28.062
A man? A dog?

170
00:11:28.228 --> 00:11:30.106
Some kind of animal?

171
00:11:30.272 --> 00:11:34.193
I-I don't know.
I don't know.

172
00:11:34.359 --> 00:11:36.473
I couldn't really get
a good look at it.

173
00:11:36.598 --> 00:11:40.200
I was so scared. I just wanted
to get out of there.

174
00:11:43.738 --> 00:11:48.675
I know that something terrible
has happened to him.

175
00:11:56.298 --> 00:11:58.461
They went to Rocky's house.
Rocky wasn't there.

176
00:11:58.586 --> 00:12:00.630
Talked to his dad.
Truck driver.

177
00:12:00.755 --> 00:12:01.797
Just got back the night before last.

178
00:12:01.922 --> 00:12:03.016
hasn't seen Rocky.

179
00:12:03.141 --> 00:12:04.601
- What about his mother?
- Died when he was a kid.

180
00:12:04.726 --> 00:12:06.035
Did he have a cell phone?

181
00:12:06.160 --> 00:12:09.489
Used to. Dad said they had
to cut back on expenses. so...

182
00:12:09.614 --> 00:12:11.040
Did he have any idea
where his son might be?

183
00:12:11.165 --> 00:12:12.041
He said if you find his pickup.

184
00:12:12.166 --> 00:12:13.243
that's where he'll be.

185
00:12:13.368 --> 00:12:14.577
Well. his truck's
already been impounded.

186
00:12:14.702 --> 00:12:17.714
Gilda was driving it last night.

187
00:12:17.839 --> 00:12:20.865
That's all I got.

188
00:12:22.744 --> 00:12:25.121
What if their little party
got out of hand. Rocky got hurt?

189
00:12:25.246 --> 00:12:26.523
Maybe he fell down the stairs.

190
00:12:26.648 --> 00:12:28.708
Maybe Gilda pushed him.
broke his neck.

191
00:12:28.833 --> 00:12:29.993
Gilda got scared.

192
00:12:30.118 --> 00:12:32.228
dumped his body in the river
or into the woods.

193
00:12:32.353 --> 00:12:33.846
Now she's trying to make it look
like she's innocent.

194
00:12:33.971 --> 00:12:35.548
I don't think she's trying
to cover anything up.

195
00:12:35.673 --> 00:12:37.967
It seems to me
she's pushing us to find him.

196
00:12:38.092 --> 00:12:39.602
I think we have to take another look

197
00:12:39.727 --> 00:12:41.354
at that house they broke into.

198
00:12:45.016 --> 00:12:46.140
Hello?

199
00:12:46.306 --> 00:12:50.346
I need to see you.
Now.

200
00:12:50.471 --> 00:12:51.562
She's very weak.

201
00:12:51.728 --> 00:12:55.316
but I realize you
may not have much time.

202
00:12:55.482 --> 00:12:58.645
I'll be right outside.

203
00:13:07.995 --> 00:13:09.997
I was afraid I lost you.

204
00:13:10.163 --> 00:13:12.201
Not yet.

205
00:13:12.326 --> 00:13:15.204
You're all I have left.

206
00:13:15.329 --> 00:13:16.796
I don't want this to happen.

207
00:13:16.962 --> 00:13:20.510
I know.
But you'll be all right.

208
00:13:20.635 --> 00:13:22.718
Yeah. I don't feel like
I'm gonna be all right.

209
00:13:22.884 --> 00:13:26.182
I'm still trying to
make sense of everything.

210
00:13:26.307 --> 00:13:29.350
Look. if you hadn't been here.
I would've lost my mind.

211
00:13:29.516 --> 00:13:32.186
I'm not sure I haven't.

212
00:13:32.352 --> 00:13:33.980
Don't doubt yourself.

213
00:13:34.146 --> 00:13:37.275
- I've seen so much.
- And you'll see more.

214
00:13:37.441 --> 00:13:41.447
You have a responsibility
that you cannot ignore.

215
00:13:41.572 --> 00:13:44.467
I couldn't ignore it if I tried.

216
00:13:44.592 --> 00:13:47.670
You have to hunt down the bad ones.

217
00:13:47.795 --> 00:13:49.973
just like your ancestors did.

218
00:13:50.098 --> 00:13:51.908
There's a reason that you're a cop.

219
00:13:52.033 --> 00:13:54.208
You have an ability.
and you must use it.

220
00:13:54.374 --> 00:13:56.878
no matter what happens to me.

221
00:13:57.044 --> 00:13:58.754
I'll go get a doctor.

222
00:13:58.920 --> 00:14:02.051
No.

223
00:14:02.176 --> 00:14:03.718
The reapers followed me here.

224
00:14:03.884 --> 00:14:05.428
That means there could be more.

225
00:14:05.594 --> 00:14:07.457
How many are there?

226
00:14:07.582 --> 00:14:09.459
Nobody knows.

227
00:14:09.584 --> 00:14:11.851
They're a secret organization
dedicated to killing us.

228
00:14:12.017 --> 00:14:15.164
You mean Grimms?
There are more like us?

229
00:14:15.289 --> 00:14:18.301
Yes. but I don't
have contact with them.

230
00:14:18.426 --> 00:14:19.819
What about the things
I've been seeing?

231
00:14:19.944 --> 00:14:21.371
How many more of those are there?

232
00:14:21.496 --> 00:14:24.040
There are more in the books
than I've ever seen.

233
00:14:24.165 --> 00:14:26.175
You must not let
the trailer be found.

234
00:14:26.300 --> 00:14:28.711
They don't know it exists.

235
00:14:28.836 --> 00:14:32.079
I hope I haven't done more harm
than good by coming to you.

236
00:14:35.707 --> 00:14:37.620
Let her rest.

237
00:14:37.745 --> 00:14:40.421
You can come back later.

238
00:14:50.758 --> 00:14:51.934
How is she?

239
00:14:52.059 --> 00:14:53.302
Well. she's dying of cancer.

240
00:14:53.427 --> 00:14:55.188
She's had two attempts made
at her life.

241
00:14:55.313 --> 00:14:57.563
Other than that.
she's doing all right.

242
00:15:00.768 --> 00:15:02.211
She's one tough lady.

243
00:15:02.336 --> 00:15:04.080
I had no idea.

244
00:15:04.205 --> 00:15:05.782
So you got anything on the Rabes?

245
00:15:05.907 --> 00:15:08.491
Yeah. Their house sits
on about 200 acres.

246
00:15:08.657 --> 00:15:10.553
backs up onto the national forest.

247
00:15:10.678 --> 00:15:12.505
500 square miles
of trees behind them.

248
00:15:12.630 --> 00:15:14.205
Lots of places for Rocky to get lost.

249
00:15:16.498 --> 00:15:18.628
These woods are too big
for the two of us.

250
00:15:18.753 --> 00:15:20.854
Let's get some people out here.

251
00:15:26.717 --> 00:15:28.386
Whoa. whoa. whoa.
whoa. whoa. Look out.

252
00:15:52.336 --> 00:15:55.121
Hey. Nice riding.

253
00:15:55.287 --> 00:15:57.750
Oh. I hope we didn't scare you.

254
00:15:57.875 --> 00:15:59.792
Oh. no. you guys are lucky
you didn't get thumped.

255
00:15:59.958 --> 00:16:01.003
Look. we knew what we were doing.

256
00:16:01.128 --> 00:16:02.221
That's a good thing.

257
00:16:02.346 --> 00:16:03.838
'cause I hate
cleaning blood off my car.

258
00:16:04.004 --> 00:16:06.442
You guys. uh. here for my parents?

259
00:16:06.715 --> 00:16:08.561
Detectives Burkhardt and Griffin.

260
00:16:08.842 --> 00:16:13.306
You're Barry Rabe.
You live here. right?

261
00:16:13.472 --> 00:16:16.269
Have you guys ever seen
either of 'em?

262
00:16:16.558 --> 00:16:18.404
Oh. no. take your time.

263
00:16:18.685 --> 00:16:21.939
Make sure you don't know them
from school or anything.

264
00:16:22.105 --> 00:16:23.357
Look. we've never seen them before.

265
00:16:23.523 --> 00:16:25.151
Boys. dinner's ready.
Wash up.

266
00:16:25.317 --> 00:16:27.320
What are you doing back here?

267
00:16:27.486 --> 00:16:29.398
Did you find out
who broke into our house?

268
00:16:29.523 --> 00:16:30.900
Yeah. I think so.

269
00:16:31.025 --> 00:16:32.241
Frank. you should come out here.

270
00:16:32.407 --> 00:16:34.587
Ma'am could you take a look at these?

271
00:16:34.712 --> 00:16:36.120
Now. the girl's already in custody.

272
00:16:36.286 --> 00:16:38.741
but we haven't seen the guy yet.

273
00:16:38.866 --> 00:16:42.378
Have you ever seen
either of these guys?

274
00:16:42.503 --> 00:16:43.412
No.

275
00:16:43.537 --> 00:16:45.715
- Yeah. me. either.
- Hey. Barry.

276
00:16:45.840 --> 00:16:47.583
you didn't happen to come home
last night. did you?

277
00:16:47.708 --> 00:16:49.969
He was staying at
Jason and T.B.'s house

278
00:16:50.094 --> 00:16:50.987
while we were gone.

279
00:16:51.112 --> 00:16:52.622
Sorry. Mrs. Rabe. we have to ask.

280
00:16:52.747 --> 00:16:53.929
Just in case he saw the boy leave.

281
00:16:54.095 --> 00:16:56.098
No. I didn't get home
till this morning.

282
00:16:56.264 --> 00:16:59.435
after my parents got back.

283
00:17:02.490 --> 00:17:05.107
No. I-I didn't see 'em.

284
00:17:05.273 --> 00:17:06.984
How far away do you guys live?

285
00:17:07.150 --> 00:17:09.038
What is this?

286
00:17:09.163 --> 00:17:10.206
Look. we're just trying to figure out

287
00:17:10.331 --> 00:17:11.307
where everybody was last night.

288
00:17:11.432 --> 00:17:12.575
We know they broke into your house.

289
00:17:12.700 --> 00:17:14.377
but no one's seen the boy
since last night.

290
00:17:14.502 --> 00:17:15.534
The girl said she heard a scream

291
00:17:15.700 --> 00:17:17.119
inside the house after she left.

292
00:17:17.285 --> 00:17:19.749
And you believe someone
who broke into our house.

293
00:17:19.874 --> 00:17:21.000
drank our wine. ate our food.

294
00:17:21.125 --> 00:17:23.452
and took advantage of our bedroom?

295
00:17:23.577 --> 00:17:26.045
I think you'd be better off
looking under a few rocks.

296
00:17:26.211 --> 00:17:29.675
Wish you'd remember
that we're the victims here.

297
00:17:29.800 --> 00:17:32.185
Boys. let's go in the house.

298
00:17:34.438 --> 00:17:36.516
If you want to talk to me.

299
00:17:36.641 --> 00:17:40.893
you can call me tomorrow
at my law firm.

300
00:17:42.647 --> 00:17:45.523
Man. we really hit a nerve.

301
00:17:50.738 --> 00:17:51.914
Let's run some phone records.

302
00:17:52.039 --> 00:17:54.740
pin down where everyone was
last night.

303
00:18:10.290 --> 00:18:11.601
She came out of the coma.

304
00:18:11.726 --> 00:18:13.050
and I've had to put guards on her.

305
00:18:13.216 --> 00:18:14.537
What do you want me to do?

306
00:18:14.662 --> 00:18:16.439
We can't allow her
to tell him anything more.

307
00:18:16.564 --> 00:18:18.389
- We need him with us.
- And how do I get to her?

308
00:18:18.555 --> 00:18:21.344
Well. you don't.
But you get somebody who can.

309
00:18:21.469 --> 00:18:22.945
With guards on her?

310
00:18:23.070 --> 00:18:25.281
Don't worry about that.
Just find the right people...

311
00:18:25.406 --> 00:18:27.817
And I do mean people.

312
00:18:27.942 --> 00:18:29.185
We can't afford
someone getting excited

313
00:18:29.310 --> 00:18:31.736
and blowing the whole thing.

314
00:18:31.902 --> 00:18:33.696
Don't you know
this is a bad neighborhood?

315
00:18:33.862 --> 00:18:36.407
How much is it worth
for you not to get hurt?

316
00:18:36.573 --> 00:18:40.062
Don't worry.
I'll take care of this.

317
00:18:50.515 --> 00:18:51.926
Nick?

318
00:18:52.051 --> 00:18:54.383
Yeah. in here.

319
00:18:54.549 --> 00:18:59.035
I picked up Chinese
from Lotus. and...

320
00:18:59.160 --> 00:19:01.599
- Got Voodoo doughnuts.
- Ah. you are the best.

321
00:19:01.765 --> 00:19:03.373
Don't be such a cop.

322
00:19:03.498 --> 00:19:05.716
The doughnuts are for dessert.

323
00:19:08.987 --> 00:19:11.064
Are we buying a totem pole?

324
00:19:11.189 --> 00:19:14.534
No. I saw one outside a house
of a case I'm working on.

325
00:19:14.659 --> 00:19:16.302
Some kind of clan of the bear.

326
00:19:16.427 --> 00:19:18.705
"The bear is a messenger
to the supernatural world.

327
00:19:18.830 --> 00:19:22.025
"His position of dominance
in the totemic hierarchy

328
00:19:22.150 --> 00:19:24.027
"is the result of
a common ancestral belief

329
00:19:24.152 --> 00:19:26.046
in the sanctity of their territory."

330
00:19:26.171 --> 00:19:27.147
Hmm.

331
00:19:27.272 --> 00:19:29.749
Is the totem pole some kind of clue?

332
00:19:29.874 --> 00:19:33.547
I don't know. but you
make it sound kind of sexy.

333
00:19:33.713 --> 00:19:36.313
- It's just the word pole.
- Mm.

334
00:19:38.082 --> 00:19:39.804
I stopped by to see Marie today.

335
00:19:39.970 --> 00:19:42.462
It scared me. seeing
all the police in the hospital.

336
00:19:42.587 --> 00:19:45.059
I don't know why anybody
would want to hurt her.

337
00:19:45.225 --> 00:19:47.801
She can't even die in peace.

338
00:19:47.926 --> 00:19:49.814
How are you doing with all that?

339
00:19:49.980 --> 00:19:52.605
Well. I'm not doing
too good about it. but...

340
00:19:52.730 --> 00:19:54.074
You know. there's nothing I can do.

341
00:19:54.199 --> 00:19:56.529
so I'm putting on my happy face.

342
00:19:56.695 --> 00:19:58.989
I'm not buying that grin.
Put it back.

343
00:20:35.974 --> 00:20:37.278
Okay. Do it.

344
00:20:37.444 --> 00:20:38.818
Uhh!

345
00:20:41.031 --> 00:20:42.279
That'll work.

346
00:21:03.261 --> 00:21:04.388
Aunt Marie.

347
00:21:04.554 --> 00:21:07.297
What are you doing here?

348
00:21:07.422 --> 00:21:10.007
Remember what I told you.

349
00:21:11.809 --> 00:21:13.772
Okay.

350
00:21:15.565 --> 00:21:17.401
There'll be more red...

351
00:21:24.105 --> 00:21:25.451
When the sun goes down.

352
00:21:36.753 --> 00:21:37.588
Uhh!

353
00:21:40.405 --> 00:21:42.927
You okay?

354
00:21:43.093 --> 00:21:44.887
Yeah.

355
00:21:45.053 --> 00:21:49.022
Yeah. just. uh...
A bad dream. I hope.

356
00:21:49.147 --> 00:21:51.014
What was it?

357
00:21:53.551 --> 00:21:56.857
My aunt just stabbed me in the hand.

358
00:21:57.023 --> 00:22:00.499
What did you do to her?

359
00:22:00.624 --> 00:22:03.102
Nope. just a dream.
But I don't even know

360
00:22:03.227 --> 00:22:05.305
where to begin interpreting that one.

361
00:22:05.430 --> 00:22:09.370
I was trying to let you sleep.
Lot of good that did.

362
00:22:13.154 --> 00:22:16.866
Hey. hey.
Where you going so early?

363
00:22:16.991 --> 00:22:19.118
I'm operating on a bulldog at 7:00.

364
00:22:19.243 --> 00:22:20.711
I'll call you later.

365
00:23:07.792 --> 00:23:09.346
You have to hunt down the bad ones.

366
00:23:43.588 --> 00:23:44.923
We need to talk.

367
00:23:45.089 --> 00:23:48.284
Not at 6:30 in the morning. we don't.

368
00:23:48.409 --> 00:23:49.618
This is important.

369
00:23:49.743 --> 00:23:52.431
Oh. well. come on in. then.
Have a cup of coffee.

370
00:23:52.597 --> 00:23:54.683
Bagel? Cream cheese?

371
00:23:54.849 --> 00:23:56.642
First. I want to thank you

372
00:23:56.767 --> 00:23:58.520
for helping me out
with the kidnapping.

373
00:23:58.686 --> 00:24:00.880
A gift basket would've been nice.

374
00:24:01.005 --> 00:24:02.081
How long is this gonna take?

375
00:24:02.206 --> 00:24:04.667
I'm right in the middle
of my Pilates. man.

376
00:24:04.792 --> 00:24:06.320
You ever seen one of these?

377
00:24:13.684 --> 00:24:15.537
Not up close. thank God.

378
00:24:18.155 --> 00:24:20.918
I think Jagerbars use these
for disemboweling.

379
00:24:21.084 --> 00:24:23.803
Now I'm hungry.

380
00:24:23.928 --> 00:24:25.130
Sure you don't want a bagel?

381
00:24:25.296 --> 00:24:27.223
I'm gonna French press
some coffee. too.

382
00:24:27.348 --> 00:24:29.426
Guatemalan highlands.
Craft roasted.

383
00:24:29.592 --> 00:24:31.510
Very robust.

384
00:24:31.635 --> 00:24:33.279
What do you know about Jagerbars?

385
00:24:33.404 --> 00:24:35.197
What am I. your personal Grimmopedia?

386
00:24:35.322 --> 00:24:36.565
No. you're a Blutbad.

387
00:24:36.690 --> 00:24:40.062
and I'm assuming that Blutbaden
know about Jagerbaden?

388
00:24:40.228 --> 00:24:42.481
It's just Jagerbars.

389
00:24:42.647 --> 00:24:44.358
Well. you see them
like I see them. right?

390
00:24:44.524 --> 00:24:46.575
Yes.

391
00:24:46.700 --> 00:24:48.043
Hey. I'm just trying to figure out

392
00:24:48.168 --> 00:24:49.378
- what I'm up against here.
- Okay.

393
00:24:49.503 --> 00:24:51.297
Right there...
Don't even compare the two.

394
00:24:51.422 --> 00:24:53.749
We don't rummage like they do.

395
00:24:53.874 --> 00:24:55.828
How'd you run across
a Jagerbar anyway?

396
00:24:55.994 --> 00:24:58.704
Look. I'm working on a case.

397
00:24:58.829 --> 00:25:00.139
I saw a kid turn into one.

398
00:25:00.264 --> 00:25:01.291
That where you got the claw?

399
00:25:01.457 --> 00:25:02.675
No. my aunt had it.

400
00:25:02.800 --> 00:25:06.078
Oh. right. Her again.
Aunt Marie. right?

401
00:25:06.203 --> 00:25:08.080
Yeah. I couldn't sleep
the last two nights

402
00:25:08.205 --> 00:25:10.182
thinking ol' aunt Marie
was gonna cut off my head.

403
00:25:10.307 --> 00:25:12.768
stick it on a lamp post.

404
00:25:12.893 --> 00:25:14.304
That's how my great grandma
ended up. you know.

405
00:25:14.561 --> 00:25:16.155
Hey. she's still in the hospital.

406
00:25:16.280 --> 00:25:20.860
Oh. Sorry. Um...

407
00:25:20.985 --> 00:25:22.795
They use those claws in the Roh-Hatz.

408
00:25:22.920 --> 00:25:23.929
Roh-Hatz?

409
00:25:24.054 --> 00:25:25.482
It's like a Bar Mitzvah for bears.

410
00:25:25.648 --> 00:25:28.300
You know. a Jagerbar Mitzvah.
It's a very physical thing.

411
00:25:28.425 --> 00:25:31.453
A lot of pounding of chests.
and. like. wailing.

412
00:25:31.578 --> 00:25:33.365
Who wails anymore?

413
00:25:33.531 --> 00:25:37.828
Supposed to connect with the
primitive beast in all of us.

414
00:25:39.586 --> 00:25:42.833
And believe me. I do mean all of us.

415
00:25:45.042 --> 00:25:46.503
So what do they do?

416
00:25:46.669 --> 00:25:49.254
- It's all about the chase.
- What chase?

417
00:25:49.379 --> 00:25:52.441
The Roh-Hatz. you know?
Caveman mumbo-jumbo.

418
00:25:52.566 --> 00:25:55.053
"Let's get some beers
and barbeque and be stupid."

419
00:25:55.552 --> 00:25:57.431
I mean. I like to camp
as much as the next guy.

420
00:25:57.597 --> 00:25:59.899
You know. maybe once a year.

421
00:26:00.024 --> 00:26:00.900
Want plain or onion?

422
00:26:01.025 --> 00:26:02.368
I gotta go.

423
00:26:02.493 --> 00:26:04.980
Oh. Well.
Thanks for stopping by.

424
00:26:12.269 --> 00:26:16.405
What are you drawing?

425
00:26:20.811 --> 00:26:23.589
Jagerbar.

426
00:26:23.714 --> 00:26:27.092
You saw one?

427
00:26:27.217 --> 00:26:28.510
Well. there was a family.

428
00:26:28.635 --> 00:26:30.088
but the boy's the only one I saw.

429
00:26:30.254 --> 00:26:32.865
- How old?
- 18.

430
00:26:32.990 --> 00:26:37.636
That could be a problem
if they're traditional.

431
00:26:37.761 --> 00:26:39.238
Anyone die?

432
00:26:39.363 --> 00:26:43.375
I don't know.
I've got aissing person.

433
00:26:43.500 --> 00:26:45.210
Do you know what the Roh-Hatz is?

434
00:26:45.335 --> 00:26:50.616
You're learning.
That's good.

435
00:26:50.741 --> 00:26:53.519
It's a rite of passage
from boy to man.

436
00:26:53.644 --> 00:26:57.423
They do it at sunset.

437
00:26:57.548 --> 00:27:01.160
It isn't pretty.

438
00:27:01.285 --> 00:27:04.581
The red of the sun
and the blood on their hands.

439
00:27:12.696 --> 00:27:13.906
Just got the phone records.

440
00:27:14.031 --> 00:27:16.241
Several calls were made
between 9:00 and midnight.

441
00:27:16.366 --> 00:27:18.694
We triangulated a call made from
Barry Rabe's cell phone

442
00:27:18.819 --> 00:27:21.246
that puts him at his house
at 11:30 that night.

443
00:27:21.371 --> 00:27:22.614
When Gilda was there with Rocky.

444
00:27:22.739 --> 00:27:23.866
Yeah. so Barry's lying.

445
00:27:23.991 --> 00:27:25.477
and lawyer dad
is running interference.

446
00:27:25.643 --> 00:27:27.319
Oh. a lawyer doing a bad thing?

447
00:27:27.444 --> 00:27:28.487
- Never heard of that before.
- Hey. Nick.

448
00:27:28.612 --> 00:27:29.955
Can I talk to you a minute?

449
00:27:30.080 --> 00:27:31.206
Yes. sir?

450
00:27:31.331 --> 00:27:32.708
Listen. I had to pull the guys
guarding your aunt

451
00:27:32.833 --> 00:27:34.193
- at the hospital.
- What?

452
00:27:34.318 --> 00:27:35.728
With no hard evidence
of a second attack.

453
00:27:35.853 --> 00:27:37.496
I couldn't justify
the expense to the chief

454
00:27:37.621 --> 00:27:39.992
without it looking like we're
giving preferential treatment

455
00:27:40.158 --> 00:27:41.785
to police families.

456
00:27:41.951 --> 00:27:44.871
I'm sorry. but my hands are tied.

457
00:28:04.248 --> 00:28:05.874
Monroe.

458
00:28:05.999 --> 00:28:07.561
Now what?

459
00:28:07.727 --> 00:28:10.362
A Grimm?
Are you out of your mind?

460
00:28:10.487 --> 00:28:11.648
I can't do this.

461
00:28:11.814 --> 00:28:13.399
Look. I just need your help

462
00:28:13.524 --> 00:28:14.735
until I can figure
something else out.

463
00:28:14.901 --> 00:28:16.236
I'm not a cop.

464
00:28:16.402 --> 00:28:18.071
Yeah. you...You're the only one
who knows what I'm...

465
00:28:18.237 --> 00:28:19.838
No. I am the only one
who is stupid enough

466
00:28:19.963 --> 00:28:21.783
to talk to you.

467
00:28:21.949 --> 00:28:22.951
I'll owe you one.

468
00:28:23.117 --> 00:28:24.286
Dude. you already owe me three.

469
00:28:24.452 --> 00:28:25.871
Three?

470
00:28:26.037 --> 00:28:27.613
Yeah. The little girl
who was kidnapped.

471
00:28:27.738 --> 00:28:30.349
the Jagerbar at 6:30 this morning

472
00:28:30.474 --> 00:28:32.051
in the middle of my Pilates.

473
00:28:32.176 --> 00:28:34.453
and now this.

474
00:28:34.578 --> 00:28:36.465
Okay. I'll owe you three.

475
00:28:36.631 --> 00:28:37.773
What the hell makes you think

476
00:28:37.898 --> 00:28:40.459
I am gonna stay here and protect her?

477
00:28:40.584 --> 00:28:42.679
Because I trust you.

478
00:28:42.845 --> 00:28:48.101
Look. I'll be back as soon as I can.

479
00:28:54.431 --> 00:28:56.026
Maybe you shouldn't trust me.

480
00:28:58.085 --> 00:28:59.178
Hey. what's up?

481
00:28:59.303 --> 00:29:01.156
Rocky's dad just called.
Gilda made bail.

482
00:29:01.322 --> 00:29:02.431
She went over to his house

483
00:29:02.556 --> 00:29:03.882
and got a gun Rocky had in his room.

484
00:29:04.007 --> 00:29:04.883
He couldn't stop her.

485
00:29:05.008 --> 00:29:06.385
Said she was gonna get Rocky back

486
00:29:06.510 --> 00:29:07.954
or kill the people that took him.

487
00:29:26.280 --> 00:29:27.406
Where is he?

488
00:29:27.531 --> 00:29:28.940
- Where is he?
- Oh. my God.

489
00:29:29.065 --> 00:29:30.375
Are you the girl
that broke into my house?

490
00:29:30.500 --> 00:29:31.743
You tell me where he is.
or I'll shoot.

491
00:29:31.868 --> 00:29:33.078
Please don't hurt me.

492
00:29:33.203 --> 00:29:34.606
I-I-I don't know what
you're talking about.

493
00:29:34.772 --> 00:29:36.608
You know where he...Aah!

494
00:29:38.859 --> 00:29:39.986
Uhh!

495
00:29:41.654 --> 00:29:44.389
Are you okay. mom?

496
00:29:44.514 --> 00:29:47.953
I am now.
And well done. son.

497
00:29:48.119 --> 00:29:50.997
Hunting two is better than one.

498
00:29:51.163 --> 00:29:53.375
You make your ancestors proud.

499
00:29:58.421 --> 00:29:59.729
Ohh!

500
00:30:03.467 --> 00:30:05.401
Get rid of her truck.

501
00:30:20.181 --> 00:30:21.182
Hi.

502
00:30:22.101 --> 00:30:23.227
Barry home?

503
00:30:23.352 --> 00:30:25.530
- No. he's out with friends.
- Doing what?

504
00:30:25.655 --> 00:30:26.848
I don't know.
Riding their bikes?

505
00:30:26.973 --> 00:30:29.035
God. I hope he doesn't
break his neck.

506
00:30:35.833 --> 00:30:37.058
What do you want?

507
00:30:37.183 --> 00:30:38.526
The woman who broke into your house

508
00:30:38.651 --> 00:30:40.495
is on her way here...
And she's not happy.

509
00:30:40.620 --> 00:30:41.696
She's got a gun.

510
00:30:41.821 --> 00:30:43.216
What? Is everything okay?

511
00:30:43.382 --> 00:30:45.260
- Everything's fine.
- I don't really think so.

512
00:30:45.426 --> 00:30:47.168
It doesn't look like she's here yet.

513
00:30:47.293 --> 00:30:48.670
I'm going back down the road.

514
00:30:48.795 --> 00:30:52.642
I'll block it off in case she shows.

515
00:30:52.808 --> 00:30:54.519
We need to talk.
Right now.

516
00:30:54.685 --> 00:30:56.813
I know what you are.
You know who I am.

517
00:30:56.979 --> 00:30:58.023
So let's cut the crap.

518
00:30:58.189 --> 00:30:59.947
You wanna cut the crap?

519
00:31:00.072 --> 00:31:02.402
Okay. You're a Grimm.

520
00:31:02.568 --> 00:31:04.404
You're a danger to my family.

521
00:31:04.570 --> 00:31:06.740
And don't think wearing a badge
is going to protect you.

522
00:31:06.906 --> 00:31:08.116
This isn't about me.

523
00:31:10.516 --> 00:31:11.726
I know about the hunt.

524
00:31:11.851 --> 00:31:13.497
- What are you talking about?
- The roh-hatz.

525
00:31:13.663 --> 00:31:16.030
- Nobody does that anymore.
- Yes. they do.

526
00:31:16.155 --> 00:31:17.165
And when the sun goes down tonight.

527
00:31:17.290 --> 00:31:18.666
it's gonna be too late.

528
00:31:18.791 --> 00:31:20.702
Look. Barry and those two boys
have got Rocky.

529
00:31:20.827 --> 00:31:23.465
and we don't have a lot of time.

530
00:31:23.631 --> 00:31:25.640
Come on. you're a lawyer.

531
00:31:25.765 --> 00:31:29.137
If they kill this innocent kid
over this stupid hunt.

532
00:31:29.303 --> 00:31:31.112
their lives are over.

533
00:31:31.237 --> 00:31:33.308
- Where are they?
- I told you.

534
00:31:33.474 --> 00:31:34.768
Where are they?

535
00:31:38.644 --> 00:31:40.232
Why don't you ask to see his warrant?

536
00:31:40.398 --> 00:31:44.986
Oh. my God.
I didn't realize.

537
00:31:45.152 --> 00:31:47.094
So what do you want to do?
You want to go inside.

538
00:31:47.219 --> 00:31:49.741
have a few drinks. forget about it?

539
00:31:49.907 --> 00:31:53.234
Or do you want to come with me?

540
00:31:53.359 --> 00:31:56.248
Okay. But we're gonna have
to take my four-Wheeler.

541
00:31:56.414 --> 00:31:57.749
You know where they are?

542
00:31:57.915 --> 00:32:00.615
I think I know where they might be.

543
00:32:19.802 --> 00:32:23.355
Requesting back-up
at 1534 Wilder road.

544
00:32:38.154 --> 00:32:40.750
If we find them. promise me
you're not gonna hurt them.

545
00:32:40.916 --> 00:32:43.167
I won't if I don't have to.

546
00:32:43.292 --> 00:32:44.713
Okay.

547
00:32:51.551 --> 00:32:52.993
It's Nick.
You got anything?

548
00:32:53.118 --> 00:32:54.662
I found the truck.
She's here somewhere.

549
00:32:54.787 --> 00:32:56.224
I'm with Frank Rabe.
I'm going after the boys.

550
00:32:56.390 --> 00:32:58.184
I'll call you if I get anything.

551
00:33:08.319 --> 00:33:09.988
We're sorry
we broke into your house.

552
00:33:10.154 --> 00:33:11.865
We'll never do it again.

553
00:33:24.460 --> 00:33:25.743
Uhh! Just let her go!

554
00:33:25.868 --> 00:33:27.464
Yeah. we'll let her go.

555
00:33:27.630 --> 00:33:28.882
We're gonna let you go. too.

556
00:33:29.048 --> 00:33:31.176
Don't worry.
We'll give you a head start.

557
00:33:33.042 --> 00:33:34.702
No. please. no.

558
00:33:34.827 --> 00:33:37.388
Oh. wow. man.
They're really scared.

559
00:33:37.513 --> 00:33:38.767
Please!

560
00:33:38.933 --> 00:33:41.466
It's ridiculous.

561
00:33:47.673 --> 00:33:50.195
You people murdered my grandfather.

562
00:33:50.361 --> 00:33:52.656
The Grimms burned down his farm.

563
00:33:52.822 --> 00:33:55.990
cut off his head.
his hands. and his feet.

564
00:33:56.115 --> 00:33:58.926
Okay. he may have deserved it
for some of the things he did.

565
00:33:59.051 --> 00:34:00.747
But if my parents could see me now.

566
00:34:00.913 --> 00:34:03.667
standing this close to you
and not avenging the family.

567
00:34:03.833 --> 00:34:08.088
last Thanksgiving I'd be
invited to. I can tell you that.

568
00:34:12.865 --> 00:34:14.969
Take your best shot. Blutbad.

569
00:34:28.566 --> 00:34:30.825
We're gonna have to
take the trail from here.

570
00:34:30.950 --> 00:34:32.310
How do you know they'll be there?

571
00:34:32.435 --> 00:34:34.436
I don't.

572
00:35:00.055 --> 00:35:01.262
Uhh!

573
00:35:04.143 --> 00:35:05.311
Guh!

574
00:35:20.983 --> 00:35:22.829
Uhh! Ohh!

575
00:35:28.125 --> 00:35:29.961
Aah!

576
00:35:35.081 --> 00:35:37.882
Okay. that went a little too far.

577
00:35:49.678 --> 00:35:51.295
There's a cave up ahead.

578
00:35:57.321 --> 00:36:00.731
Let me go first.
try and talk them out.

579
00:36:00.856 --> 00:36:02.283
No.

580
00:36:02.408 --> 00:36:04.954
I'm either coming with you.
or I'm going alone.

581
00:36:26.098 --> 00:36:27.018
We're too late.

582
00:36:35.442 --> 00:36:37.601
It's started.

583
00:36:48.904 --> 00:36:50.688
Come on. get up!

584
00:37:17.164 --> 00:37:18.069
Get out!

585
00:37:20.268 --> 00:37:22.907
Aah! Uhh!

586
00:37:26.841 --> 00:37:29.289
This isn't gonna get any better
unless you stop.

587
00:37:29.455 --> 00:37:32.750
No! Barry! Son!
This is over.

588
00:37:34.043 --> 00:37:35.086
Stay down.

589
00:37:36.837 --> 00:37:39.896
It stops now.

590
00:37:40.021 --> 00:37:41.009
No!

591
00:37:41.175 --> 00:37:43.616
Mom! Don't!

592
00:38:09.717 --> 00:38:11.127
Mom.

593
00:38:11.252 --> 00:38:12.495
Mom...Please.

594
00:38:12.620 --> 00:38:14.781
I am so sorry.

595
00:38:14.906 --> 00:38:16.586
You did nothing wrong.

596
00:38:16.752 --> 00:38:18.785
Yeah. he did. Diane.

597
00:38:18.910 --> 00:38:21.704
And now we're all
gonna have to pay for it.

598
00:38:21.829 --> 00:38:23.927
You have to respect your ancestors.

599
00:38:24.093 --> 00:38:25.970
Not like this.

600
00:38:40.192 --> 00:38:42.559
Okay. let's see. we got kidnapping

601
00:38:42.684 --> 00:38:45.195
and attempted murder
for Barry. Jason. and t.B.

602
00:38:45.320 --> 00:38:47.700
Breaking and entering
for Rocky and Gilda.

603
00:38:47.866 --> 00:38:49.410
Well. at least
they weren't doing drugs.

604
00:38:49.576 --> 00:38:51.258
Detective.

605
00:38:54.829 --> 00:38:57.073
She wanted them
to know their heritage.

606
00:38:57.198 --> 00:39:00.076
She never understood
the danger of it.

607
00:39:00.201 --> 00:39:04.214
It isn't easy
to give up your history.

608
00:39:04.339 --> 00:39:06.552
You haven't had to give up yours.

609
00:39:06.718 --> 00:39:09.986
Yeah.
It's been a lot of fun.

610
00:39:11.796 --> 00:39:13.267
Hello?

611
00:39:13.433 --> 00:39:17.146
You told me to protect her.
And I did. but...

612
00:39:17.312 --> 00:39:18.561
Get me four units of o-positive.

613
00:39:18.686 --> 00:39:20.330
I think I may have gone
a little overboard.

614
00:39:20.455 --> 00:39:22.932
Trauma surgeon
to O.R. one. stat.

615
00:39:23.057 --> 00:39:24.968
Trauma surgeon to O.R. one. stat.

616
00:39:25.093 --> 00:39:26.019
Look. I can't stick around.

617
00:39:26.144 --> 00:39:27.737
Things are getting a little dicey.

618
00:39:27.862 --> 00:39:30.410
And you should get down here.
I'm not sure I got all of 'em.

619
00:40:01.095 --> 00:40:02.071
Oh!

620
00:40:02.196 --> 00:40:03.973
Get security up here!

621
00:40:14.108 --> 00:40:15.692
Uhh!

622
00:40:27.889 --> 00:40:29.343
Remember who you are.

623
00:40:29.509 --> 00:40:33.560
Trust your instincts
and nothing else.

624
00:40:38.800 --> 00:40:40.605
No.

625
00:40:43.671 --> 00:40:45.305
Marie.

626
00:40:48.309 --> 00:40:49.910
Come on.

627
00:41:34.255 --> 00:41:36.119
Rest well.

628
00:41:36.285 --> 00:41:38.162
Are you all right?

629
00:41:38.328 --> 00:41:41.415
No.

630
00:41:50.304 --> 00:41:51.872
But I will be.

631
00:42:07.816 --> 00:42:12.559
